[White "1. Fundamental Principles"]
[Black "Minimise Pawn Moves Where You Castle"]
[Result "*"]

{ @@HeaderStart@@Minimise Pawn Moves Where You Castle@@HeaderEnd@@In this game, we will see what happens when Black moves his Kingside pawns and castles Kingside. }
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 d5 4. c3 h6 5. Bh4 g5
{ A move as committal as ...g5 should indicate that Black will be castling Queenside - The Kingside is much too exposed! }
6. Bg3 Bg7 7. Nbd2 O-O
{ The Black King does not have good protection. Now the g5 pawn serves as an anchor for White to attack the King with h4! }
8. e3 b6 9. Ne5 Bb7 10. h4
{ The h-file will open unless Black gives up the g5 pawn with 10...g4. Either way, the Black King is extremely weak. }
10... g4 11. Nxg4 Nxg4 12. Qxg4
{ Thanks to Black's exposed King, White has an easy attacking plan as highlighted by the arrows. }
