3. Nc3 g6
{ 3...e6  This is a much better option for Black. The idea is to reinforce control over some light squares in the centre while liberating the dark-squared Bishop - A multi-purpose move  4.Nf3  Bb4  By pressuring the c3 Knight, Black exerts more pressure on the central light squares. The two Bishops are working together harmoniously and Black's opening can be considered GOOD to OFF BEAT. }
4. Nf3 Bg7
{ Black has not moved any of his central pawns. Even if they, for example, play ...e6 at some point, it loses its multi-purpose value since they have already invested time putting their dark-squared Bishop on g7. Overall, White's play is PERFECT while Black's play is OFF-BEAT or DUBIOUS. }
