1. c4 e5 2. g3 Nc6 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bc5
{ Both sides brought their Knights to central squares and Bishops to open diagonals. }
5. e3 { Preparing d4. } 5... O-O 6. Nge2
{ Supporting d4 while leaving the g2 Bishop unblocked. } 6... d5
{ Opening the centre and liberating the light-squared Bishop. } 7. cxd5
{ Black will easily win the pawn back. } 7... Nb4 { Threatening Nd3+ } 8. O-O
Nbxd5 9. Nxd5 Nxd5 10. d4 { White continues with their plan since 5. e3. }
10... exd4 11. Nxd4 { Overall, sound and PERFECT play on both sides. } *

