{ Black has just won the d4 pawn and should now be looking for a new target. What soft spots are there in White's camp? }
12... Be7
{ Going for the h4-e1 diagonal. If White wants to stop ...Bh4+, he must play h2-h4, which will only create more kingside weaknesses. Besides ...Be7 Black has a number of alternatives, each taking advantage of a different White weakness.   12...Rc8  Using the c-file well before White can connect his Rooks   12...Nb3  Using the b3 outpost, followed by the a7-g1 diagonal, is also good }
