[SetUp "1"]

{ Black just played ...b5. Is ...b4 a concern? } 17. a3
{ Patient play to take away the opponent's counterplay. The idea is that Black can only push his b-pawn on the condition he is willing to isolate his a-pawn and put his Knight on b4. This will mean the Knight is a little far from its favourite c5 square, where it can attack e4.   17.Nce2  exd4  18.Nxd4  Nc5 }
17... b4 18. axb4 Nxb4 19. Nce2
{ White's Knights are nicely supporting the centre and he is ready to reinforce it with c3. Additionally, the b4 Knight is a little far from its desired c5 square. }
