6. Bf6
{ The engine points out that this is not just a cheap attempt to get a quick mate, but in fact, a strong strategical move that prevents both the e7 Knight and the g-pawn from moving for quite a while. Alternatively, White can just take on e7 next move to force Black to take a ghastly pawn structure. }
6... d6 7. Nxe7
{ 7.e4  White can also just continue with normal development. Black is still tied up on the kingside and can't take the Bishop because of smothered mate. }
7... gxf6 { 7...Bxe7  Loses the g7 pawn  8.Bxg7 } 8. Nxc8
{ 8.Nxc8  Qxc8  Black's pawn structure allows White to use the f4 and d5 square for the Knight.  9.Nh3  The Knight is headed to f4. }
