[SetUp "1"]

{ Carlsen played 18.f5 and his opponent responded with 18...Bg7. What's the follow up ? }
19. f5 { Opening the e-file and/or the a2-g8 diagonal. } 19... exf5
{ 19...gxf5??  Hangs the Bishop.  20.Qxg7 } 20. Bc7
{ Getting the Bishop off the e-file with tempo. This ensures that Re1 will come with check and Black will be unable to castle. }
20... Qc8 21. Qd6
{ The Queen transforms into a fearsome attacker whilst preventing Black from castling. }
21... Ne4 22. Rae1
{ Pinning the e4 Knight. White will go Rxe4 to open the f-file and follow with an onslaught on f7. }
22... Qd7 23. Rxe4+ fxe4 24. Bxf7+ Qxf7 25. Rxf7 Kxf7 26. Qd7+ Kf6 27. Be5+
{ Maintaining the initiative while Black is poorly coordinated. Mate is coming soon. }
