{ Black just played Nbd7 to challenge White's strong e5 Knight. How should he respond ? }
8. f4
{ This is the best move. It maintains control over the centre without ever allowing Black to trade Queens.   8.Be3  This move is slightly weaker because it allows a Queen trade. But there's a lot more to it than meets the eye.  8...Nxe5  9.dxe5  Qxd1+  10.Rxd1  With many pieces already developed, it appears that White should be comfortably better, especially at the Grandmaster level. However, Black has the move ....  10...Ng4  Hitting e3 and e5.  11.Bd4   11.Bf4  g5  12.Bxg5  Nxe5  Black can get some activity with Rg8 or Bg7.  f6  12.exf6  exf6  White is still better, but at least Black isn't suffocated. }
8... Nxe5 9. fxe5
{ White has a tremendous centre and is substantially better. } *

