[SetUp "1"]

{ In the actual game, Black played O-O-O to trap the b7 Rook. } 15. Rxb4
{ A simple way to own the b-file.   15.Ba6?  Our light-squared Bishop is vital in accessing the Black King on c8. We can't afford to trade it off like that.  15...Qxa6  16.Rxb4  Nb6  White is still winning, but Black's light square weaknesses are significantly less problematic. }
15... Qxb4 16. Ba6+
{ 16.Rb1  Qa5  The Bishop can't go to a6, which means the Rook can't land on b7. }
16... Kc7 17. Rb1 Qd6 18. Rb7+
{ The Bishop and Rook work beautifully together. } 18... Kc8 *

