[SetUp "1"]

{ White obviously has a great position, but what's the plan? } 8. h4
{ Black is severely underdeveloped and we must expose that by opening the position. Based on the structure, the easiest place to trade pawns is the Kingside and centre.   8.g4?  e5  Attacking both the e5 Bishop and g4 pawn. We can't leave our pawn unprotected on g4 until we figure a way to parry this discovered attack. }
8... h6 9. O-O-O
{ We want to play g4-g5 to open the position. Hence, our King belongs on the Queenside. }
9... O-O 10. g4
{ Now that Black has castled, White need not fear ...e5.   10.g4  e5?  The e6 pawn was responsible for blocking the a2-g8 diagonal. Now, the f7 Knight is pinned and h6 is hanging.  11.Bxh6  Bxh6  12.Qxh6 }
*

