{ How can we defend against the onslaught on g6 and the h-file? } 14... Nh8
{ 14...Nh8  This is the toughest defence. First of all, White must deal with his hanging f4 Bishop. Furthermore, if White ever sacrifices on g6, Black will play Nhxg6, park the King on f7, and transfer the f8 Rook to h8.  15.Be3  c6  16.Nxg6  Nhxg6  17.Qxh5  Kf7  18.Bd3  Rh8  White is probably winning here, but Black is making White work hard to justify the piece sacrifice. }
