[SetUp "1"]

{ When opening the position, we must consider our final goal. Why precisely are you trying to open the position? What are you going after specifically? }
11. exf6
{ We want to open the e-file and challenge Black's royal pieces. Hence, our moves should centre around getting rid of the e5 and e6 pawns as quickly as possible.   11.Nxd5  Taking on d5 with the Knight or Bishop first also works. The idea is to rid Black of their e6 pawn so that we can win on the e-file. }
11... Bxf6 12. Bxd5
{ 12.Nxd5  Taking on d5 with the Knight to win on the e-file works as well.  12...exd5  13.Rhe1 }
12... exd5 13. Nxd5 { Going after c7. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
