[SetUp "1"]

{ White is a little better thanks to his centre control. How should he complete development? }
10. Bb5+
{ First, inconveniencing Black's Queenside development while highlighting the weakness of the a4-e8 diagonal. Black must keep an eye on the diagonal for as long as his King is uncastled. }
10... Bc6
{ This is the only tactically sound move.   10...Nd7?  11.Ne5  Bc8  A sad necessity.  12.Bf4  White is significantly more active here.   10...Nc6?  11.Qa4  With d5, Ne5, and potentially Qxa7 on the cards, Black will struggle to find a defence. }
11. Bd3
{ The Bf1-b5-d3 dance has given Black a 'free' tempo, which was forcibly spent on ...Bc6. This benefits White since moves like Ne5 and d5 will come with tempo. Furthermore, the b8 Knight is deprived of the c6 square. }
