{ What should White do if Black defends the diagonal with 16...Bc6? } 17. Bf4
{ First, gain a free tempo on the Queen. } 17... Qb7
{ 17...Qxf4  If the Bishop is taken, then the c6 Bishop will fall.  18.Bxc6  O-O-O  This is the only way to preserve the Knight. However, the light squares surrounding Black's King are especially weak.  19.a4  Black must contend with the a5 pawn break. }
18. Bxc6 { Now all that is left is to trade Bishops and dominate the e-file. }
18... Qxc6 19. Re1
{ Black can't castle and White owns the whole centre. The Queenside Rook will slide to d1. }
