[SetUp "1"]

{ Black just played 10...b5. How should we proceed? } 11. cxb5
{ Creating a weakness on b5. Indeed, this opens the a-file for Black but it would not be of much use if handled carefully. }
11... axb5 12. Bb2
{ Defending the a1 Rook to remove Black's pin along the a-file. Now, the threat is to take on b5 and Black must misplace a piece to defend it.   12.Bxb5  Nxb4??  All that remains is an open Queenside which Black can exploit more easily - All of his minor pieces are there to exploit the a3 weakness and more. }
