[SetUp "1"]

{ The Black King has lost its right to castle. What are the targets and how do we strike? }
20. e4
{ Opening up the position to go for the tender light squares around Black's King. }
20... dxe4 21. Bxe4
{ Our strategical targets are the light squares, and Black's h7 Bishop is the key defender. Hence, we seek to trade Bishops. In any case, our Bishop on g2 was not particularly useful.   21.Rxe4?  This move is only good if Black takes the Rook. Otherwise, White simply has a hard time bringing sufficient firepower to the light squares.  21...Re8  While White remains dominant, the advantage is less obvious. }
