[SetUp "1"]

{ White is a little bit more active, but Black is almost ready to complete his development. What can we do? }
14. Rfe1
{ Reinforcing control over e4 to tactically discourage Black from castling. }
14... O-O { Let's say Black castles. } 15. Bxf6
{ Eliminating the defender of d7. } 15... Bxf6 16. Nd7 Qd5
{ Black must move the Queen with a threat so that he would have time to save the f8 Rook. }
17. Qe4
{ Defending mate while threatening mate on h7, forcing the Queen trade. This move was only made possible by 14.Rfe1. }
17... Qxe4 18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Rxe4
{ 19.Nxf8?  Bc6  Our Knight is trapped and Black will have two Bishops for the Rook and pawn. }
19... Rfd8 20. Nxb6
{ Finally, snatching a pawn. White's Queenside majority will decide the game. }
