{ In the game, Black played 14...Qd5 instead. He is threatening mate, controlling e4, and ready to castle next. What is the best defence? }
15. Qf1
{ The neatest way to defend the mate because White, yet again, tactically prevents Black from castling by unleashing the e1 Rook on the e4 square.   15.f3  O-O  16.Bxf6  Bxf6  17.Be4  Qxe5  18.Bxb7  Both Black's Queen and Rook are hanging, but Black can save the Queen first, then the Rook. Hence, the Queen needs to leave the e2 square on move 15 while defending g2.  18...Qxe2  19.Rxe2  Ra7 }
15... O-O 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. Be4 Qxe5 18. Bxb7
{ Both Black's Queen and Rook are hanging.     18.Bxh7+??  Kxh7  19.Rxe5  Bxe5    Black has a Rook and two Bishops for the Queen and pawn. }
