{ Black tried 15...Bd6 in an attempt to kick our strong Knight. Can Black finally castle? }
16. Bf4
{ No! Black cannot castle because we pressure the targets along the d-file. }
16... O-O { The actual game continued   16...Qc5  17.Rad1  Bc7  18.b4  Qe7 }
17. Rad1 { Black's Queen and dark-squared Bishop are both extremely clumsy. }
17... Qc5 18. Nd7
{ A neat tactic! We are forking Queen and Rook, so this Knight must be taken. }
18... Nxd7 19. Bxd6 { We regain our piece and fork Queen and Rook yet again. }
19... Qxd6 20. Bxh7+
{ Unleashing a discovered attack on the Queen. Notice how the f4 Bishop and d1 Rook coordinated to make this entire combination possible. }
20... Kxh7 21. Rxd6 *

