{ A couple of moves later, Black thinks he is finally ready to castle. But all that time spent on Black's Queen and dark-squared Bishop has allowed White to develop EVERY piece. All that's left is to find one or more weaknesses. What are Black's weaknesses? }
19. Bb5+
{ Black's weaknesses are the a4-e8 diagonal and his vulnerable King. The reason is that all our pieces are surrounding his uncastled King and the only clear way in is through the diagonal. }
19... axb5 20. Qxb5+ Kf8 21. Nd7+
{ Unleashing a discovered attack on Black's dark-squared Bishop to dramatically weaken Black's dark squares. }
21... Nxd7 22. Bxc7 { The threats are Bd6 pin or simply taking on d7. } 22...
Ke8 23. Bxb6
{ Now that the d7 Knight is pinned, White takes the b6 pawn to not only win material, but also allow the b5 Queen to go after the b7 Bishop. White has a huge advantage and won in another 15 moves.   23...Ba6  is not a huge concern. White can consolidate with  24.Qa4  Bb7  25.Ba5  Black can no longer harass White's coordination. }
